{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "RUT"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Ruth \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Book of Ruth \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Ruth \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Rut \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Book of \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Ruth \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "RUT 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "RUT 1:1"}, "In the days when the judges judged, there was a famine in the land. A certain man of Bethlehem Judah went to live in the\ncountry of Moab with his wife and his two sons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "RUT 1:2"}, "The name of the man was Elimelech, and the name of his wife Naomi. The names of his two sons were Mahlon and Chilion,\nEphrathites of Bethlehem Judah. They came into the country of Moab and lived there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "RUT 1:3"}, "Elimelech, Naomi\u2019s husband, died; and she was left with her two sons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "RUT 1:4"}, "They took for themselves wives of the women of Moab. The name of the one was Orpah, and the name of the other was Ruth.\nThey lived there about ten years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "RUT 1:5"}, "Mahlon and Chilion both died, and the woman was bereaved of her two children and of her husband.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "RUT 1:6"}, "Then she arose with her daughters-in-law, that she might return from the country of Moab; for she had heard in the country\nof Moab how the LORD ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s\nProper Name."]}], "caller": "+"}, " had visited his people in giving them bread. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "RUT 1:7"}, "She went out of the place where she was, and her two daughters-in-law with her. They went on the way to return to the land\nof Judah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "RUT 1:8"}, "Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, \u201cGo, return each of you to her mother\u2019s house. May the LORD deal kindly with you,\nas you have dealt with the dead and with me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "RUT 1:9"}, "May The LORD grant you that you may find rest, each of you in the house of her husband.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then she kissed them, and they lifted up their voices, and wept.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "RUT 1:10"}, "They said to her, \u201cNo, but we will return with you to your people.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "RUT 1:11"}, "Naomi said, \u201cGo back, my daughters. Why do you want to go with me? Do I still have sons in my womb, that they may be your\nhusbands? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "RUT 1:12"}, "Go back, my daughters, go your way; for I am too old to have a husband. If I should say, \u2018I have hope,\u2019 if I should even\nhave a husband tonight, and should also bear sons, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "RUT 1:13"}, "would you then wait until they were grown? Would you then refrain from having husbands? No, my daughters, for it grieves\nme seriously for your sakes, for the LORD\u2019s hand has gone out against me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "RUT 1:14"}, "They lifted up their voices and wept again; then Orpah kissed her mother-in-law, but Ruth stayed with her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "RUT 1:15"}, "She said, \u201cBehold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is\noften used as an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " your sister-in-law has gone back to her people and to her god. Follow your sister-in-law.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "RUT 1:16"}, "Ruth said, \u201cDon\u2019t urge me to leave you, and to return from following you, for where you go, I will go; and where you\nstay, I will stay. Your people will be my people, and your Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d (Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " my Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "RUT 1:17"}, "Where you die, I will die, and there I will be buried. May The LORD do so to me, and more also, if anything but death\nparts you and me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "RUT 1:18"}, "When Naomi saw that she was determined to go with her, she stopped urging her.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "RUT 1:19"}, "So they both went until they came to Bethlehem. When they had come to Bethlehem, all the city was excited about them, and\nthey asked, \u201cIs this Naomi?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "RUT 1:20"}, "She said to them, \u201cDon\u2019t call me Naomi.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cNaomi\u201d means\n\u201cpleasant\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " Call me Mara,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cMara\u201d means \u201cbitter\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " for the Almighty has dealt very bitterly with me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "RUT 1:21"}, "I went out full, and the LORD has brought me home again empty. Why do you call me Naomi, since the LORD has testified\nagainst me, and the Almighty has afflicted me?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "RUT 1:22"}, "So Naomi returned, and Ruth the Moabitess, her daughter-in-law, with her, who returned out of the country of Moab. They\ncame to Bethlehem in the beginning of barley harvest. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "RUT 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "RUT 2:1"}, "Naomi had a relative of her husband\u2019s, a mighty man of wealth, of the family of Elimelech, and his name was Boaz.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "RUT 2:2"}, "Ruth the Moabitess said to Naomi, \u201cLet me now go to the field, and glean amongst the ears of grain after him in whose\nsight I find favour.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said to her, \u201cGo, my daughter.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "RUT 2:3"}, "She went, and came and gleaned in the field after the reapers; and she happened to come to the portion of the field\nbelonging to Boaz, who was of the family of Elimelech. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "RUT 2:4"}, "Behold, Boaz came from Bethlehem, and said to the reapers, \u201cMay The LORD be with you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They answered him, \u201cMay The LORD bless you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "RUT 2:5"}, "Then Boaz said to his servant who was set over the reapers, \u201cWhose young lady is this?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "RUT 2:6"}, "The servant who was set over the reapers answered, \u201cIt is the Moabite lady who came back with Naomi out of the country of\nMoab. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "RUT 2:7"}, "She said, \u2018Please let me glean and gather after the reapers amongst the sheaves.\u2019 So she came, and has continued even from\nthe morning until now, except that she rested a little in the house.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "RUT 2:8"}, "Then Boaz said to Ruth, \u201cListen, my daughter. Don\u2019t go to glean in another field, and don\u2019t go from here, but stay here\nclose to my maidens. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "RUT 2:9"}, "Let your eyes be on the field that they reap, and go after them. Haven\u2019t I commanded the young men not to touch you? When\nyou are thirsty, go to the vessels, and drink from that which the young men have drawn.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "RUT 2:10"}, "Then she fell on her face and bowed herself to the ground, and said to him, \u201cWhy have I found favour in your sight, that\nyou should take knowledge of me, since I am a foreigner?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "RUT 2:11"}, "Boaz answered her, \u201cI have been told all about what you have done for your mother-in-law since the death of your husband,\nand how you have left your father, your mother, and the land of your birth, and have come to a people that you didn\u2019t know\nbefore. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "RUT 2:12"}, "May the LORD repay your work, and a full reward be given to you from the LORD, Allah of Israel, under whose wings you\nhave come to take refuge.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "RUT 2:13"}, "Then she said, \u201cLet me find favour in your sight, my lord, because you have comforted me, and because you have spoken\nkindly to your servant, though I am not as one of your servants.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "RUT 2:14"}, "At meal time Boaz said to her, \u201cCome here, and eat some bread, and dip your morsel in the vinegar.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She sat beside the reapers, and they passed her parched grain. She ate, was satisfied, and left some of it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "RUT 2:15"}, "When she had risen up to glean, Boaz commanded his young men, saying, \u201cLet her glean even amongst the sheaves, and don\u2019t\nreproach her. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "RUT 2:16"}, "Also pull out some for her from the bundles, and leave it. Let her glean, and don\u2019t rebuke her.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "RUT 2:17"}, "So she gleaned in the field until evening; and she beat out that which she had gleaned, and it was about an\nephah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of barley. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "RUT 2:18"}, "She took it up, and went into the city. Then her mother-in-law saw what she had gleaned; and she brought out and gave to\nher that which she had left after she had enough. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "RUT 2:19"}, "Her mother-in-law said to her, \u201cWhere have you gleaned today? Where have you worked? Blessed be he who noticed you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She told her mother-in-law with whom she had worked, \u201cThe man\u2019s name with whom I worked today is Boaz.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "RUT 2:20"}, "Naomi said to her daughter-in-law, \u201cMay he be blessed by the LORD, who has not abandoned his kindness to the living and\nto the dead.\u201d Naomi said to her, \u201cThe man is a close relative to us, one of our near kinsmen.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "RUT 2:21"}, "Ruth the Moabitess said, \u201cYes, he said to me, \u2018You shall stay close to my young men until they have finished all my\nharvest.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "RUT 2:22"}, "Naomi said to Ruth her daughter-in-law, \u201cIt is good, my daughter, that you go out with his maidens, and that they not\nmeet you in any other field.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "RUT 2:23"}, "So she stayed close to the maidens of Boaz, to glean to the end of barley harvest and of wheat harvest; and she lived\nwith her mother-in-law. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "RUT 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "RUT 3:1"}, "Naomi her mother-in-law said to her, \u201cMy daughter, shall I not seek rest for you, that it may be well with you?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "RUT 3:2"}, "Now isn\u2019t Boaz our kinsman, with whose maidens you were? Behold, he will be winnowing barley tonight on the threshing\nfloor. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "RUT 3:3"}, "Therefore wash yourself, anoint yourself, get dressed, and go down to the threshing floor; but don\u2019t make yourself known\nto the man until he has finished eating and drinking. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "RUT 3:4"}, "It shall be, when he lies down, that you shall note the place where he is lying. Then you shall go in, uncover his feet,\nand lay down. Then he will tell you what to do.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "RUT 3:5"}, "She said to her, \u201cAll that you say, I will do.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "RUT 3:6"}, "She went down to the threshing floor, and did everything that her mother-in-law told her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "RUT 3:7"}, "When Boaz had eaten and drunk, and his heart was merry, he went to lie down at the end of the heap of grain. She came\nsoftly, uncovered his feet, and laid down. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "RUT 3:8"}, "At midnight, the man was startled and turned himself; and behold, a woman lay at his feet.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "RUT 3:9"}, "He said, \u201cWho are you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She answered, \u201cI am Ruth your servant. Therefore spread the corner of your garment over your servant; for you are a near\nkinsman.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "RUT 3:10"}, "He said, \u201cYou are blessed by the LORD, my daughter. You have shown more kindness in the latter end than at the beginning,\nbecause you didn\u2019t follow young men, whether poor or rich. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "RUT 3:11"}, "Now, my daughter, don\u2019t be afraid. I will do to you all that you say; for all the city of my people knows that you are a\nworthy woman. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "RUT 3:12"}, "Now it is true that I am a near kinsman. However, there is a kinsman nearer than I.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "RUT 3:13"}, "Stay this night, and in the morning, if he will perform for you the part of a kinsman, good. Let him do the kinsman\u2019s\nduty. But if he will not do the duty of a kinsman for you, then I will do the duty of a kinsman for you, as the LORD lives. Lie\ndown until the morning.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "RUT 3:14"}, "She lay at his feet until the morning, then she rose up before one could discern another. For he said, \u201cLet it not be\nknown that the woman came to the threshing floor.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "RUT 3:15"}, "He said, \u201cBring the mantle that is on you, and hold it.\u201d She held it; and he measured six measures of barley, and laid it\non her; then he went into the city. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "RUT 3:16"}, "When she came to her mother-in-law, she said, \u201cHow did it go, my daughter?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She told her all that the man had done for her. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "RUT 3:17"}, "She said, \u201cHe gave me these six measures of barley; for he said, \u2018Don\u2019t go empty to your mother-in-law.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "RUT 3:18"}, "Then she said, \u201cWait, my daughter, until you know what will happen; for the man will not rest until he has settled this\ntoday.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "RUT 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "RUT 4:1"}, "Now Boaz went up to the gate and sat down there. Behold, the near kinsman of whom Boaz spoke came by. Boaz said to him,\n\u201cCome over here, friend, and sit down!\u201d He came over, and sat down.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "RUT 4:2"}, "Boaz took ten men of the elders of the city, and said, \u201cSit down here,\u201d and they sat down.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "RUT 4:3"}, "He said to the near kinsman, \u201cNaomi, who has come back out of the country of Moab, is selling the parcel of land, which\nwas our brother Elimelech\u2019s. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "RUT 4:4"}, "I thought I should tell you, saying, \u2018Buy it before those who sit here, and before the elders of my people.\u2019 If you will\nredeem it, redeem it; but if you will not redeem it, then tell me, that I may know. For there is no one to redeem it besides\nyou; and I am after you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI will redeem it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "RUT 4:5"}, "Then Boaz said, \u201cOn the day you buy the field from the hand of Naomi, you must buy it also from Ruth the Moabitess, the\nwife of the dead, to raise up the name of the dead on his inheritance.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "RUT 4:6"}, "The near kinsman said, \u201cI can\u2019t redeem it for myself, lest I endanger my own inheritance. Take my right of redemption for\nyourself; for I can\u2019t redeem it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "RUT 4:7"}, "Now this was the custom in former time in Israel concerning redeeming and concerning exchanging, to confirm all things: a\nman took off his sandal, and gave it to his neighbour; and this was the way of formalizing transactions in Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "RUT 4:8"}, "So the near kinsman said to Boaz, \u201cBuy it for yourself,\u201d then he took off his sandal.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "RUT 4:9"}, "Boaz said to the elders and to all the people, \u201cYou are witnesses today, that I have bought all that was Elimelech\u2019s, and\nall that was Chilion\u2019s and Mahlon\u2019s, from the hand of Naomi. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "RUT 4:10"}, "Moreover, Ruth the Moabitess, the wife of Mahlon, I have purchased to be my wife, to raise up the name of the dead on his\ninheritance, that the name of the dead may not be cut off from amongst his brothers and from the gate of his place. You are\nwitnesses today.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "RUT 4:11"}, "All the people who were in the gate, and the elders, said, \u201cWe are witnesses. May the LORD make the woman who has come\ninto your house like Rachel and like Leah, which both built the house of Israel; and treat you worthily in Ephrathah, and be\nfamous in Bethlehem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "RUT 4:12"}, "Let your house be like the house of Perez, whom Tamar bore to Judah, of the\noffspring", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " which the LORD will give you by this young woman.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "RUT 4:13"}, "So Boaz took Ruth and she became his wife; and he went in to her, and the LORD enabled her to conceive, and she bore a\nson. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "RUT 4:14"}, "The women said to Naomi, \u201cBlessed be the LORD, who has not left you today without a near kinsman. Let his name be famous\nin Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "RUT 4:15"}, "He shall be to you a restorer of life and sustain you in your old age; for your daughter-in-law, who loves you, who is\nbetter to you than seven sons, has given birth to him.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "RUT 4:16"}, "Naomi took the child, laid him in her bosom, and became nurse to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "RUT 4:17"}, "The women, her neighbours, gave him a name, saying, \u201cA son is born to Naomi\u201d. They named him Obed. He is the father of\nJesse, the father of Dawood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "RUT 4:18"}, "Now this is the history of the generations of Perez: Perez became the father of Hezron,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "RUT 4:19"}, "and Hezron became the father of Ram, and Ram became the father of Amminadab,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "RUT 4:20"}, "and Amminadab became the father of Nahshon, and Nahshon became the father of Salmon,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "RUT 4:21"}, "and Salmon became the father of Boaz, and Boaz became the father of Obed,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "RUT 4:22"}, "and Obed became the father of Jesse, and Jesse became the father of Dawood.\n"]}]}